title: For Sale/Trade:  Bullwhip
postcontent: This whip is all 550 cord except for the cracker and wood base handle.  The cracker is made from 8 stands of braided fishing line.  The whip is 3 layers with 9 inches of ball bearings after the handle.  The final 550 layer starts with 4 strands (4 plait) and ends in 16 strands at the handle.  Very loud, very easy to crack, and very dangerous on the business end. The whip without the fall is about 7 1/2 feet.  There is no black tape or weird things inside this whip....just 550 cord.  If you search the internet for comparable whips, you will see these go for a bit of money.

The CZ 75 SP-01 is the first full size handgun (4.61” bbl) from CZ to feature the improved manufacturing technology and ergonomics of the NATO-approved CZ 75 Compact P-01 model. Featuring an integral 1913 accessory rail on the dust cover, rubber grip panels, and CZ’s corrosion resistant black polycoat finish, the SP-01 is the newest model to join the family of pistols based on the CZ 75 (SA/DA) platform. Borrowing from the improved grip geometry of the compact P-01, the SP-01 utilizes an extended beavertail to protect shooter’s strong hand as well as allowing for a deeper and more secure grip. The new grip geometry, checkering in key areas on the front and back straps, and redistribution of mass provided by the accessory rail noticeably decrease the perceived recoil from previous models and allows for more rapid target acquisition and transition.

The SP-01 was designed as a military and law enforcement duty sidearm. The new model is currently in use by security forces fighting the war on terrorism. Thanks to its exceptional accuracy and superior handling characteristics, the CZ 75 SP-01 has also found supporters in the field of sport and target shooting. Its list of users on the competition circuit include World Champions Adam Tyc and Angus Hobdell (1st and 3rd place respectively in 2005‘s IPSC championship, World Shoot XIV).

title: For Sale:  ACR Conversion Kit - 6.5 Grendel
postcontent:
This is a 6.5 Grendel conversion kit, done by Mike at Argonauts ReInc. The barrel is Alexander Arms, 18" long with a 1/7.5 twist. The kit includes the Argonauts 7.62/6.5 bolt that the barrel was headspaced to. In addition, I'll throw in two C Products 5 round Grendel mags. The barrel has somewhere on the order of 300 ~ 350 rounds through it. All told, the kit has cost me around $1000 to assemble. The price I'm asking is barely more that enough to cover the parts involved. The Bushmaster gas system alone is worth over $400.

Things to note:
- There is a small brass shim under the front of the gas block to level it, this insures that the op rod rides smoothly.
- The gas block has been modified to be adjustable via set screw.
- The gas port is too large, in order for proper functioning the regulator should be set to the "S" setting.
- The barrel was short chambered from the factory and had to be throated by my smith. Consequently, it is no longer a SAAMI spec Grendel chamber, instead more akin to the Saturn "Grendel II". On the plus side, it no longer jams factory ammo hard into the lands
